    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>[In nomine domini Dei eterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21"
                            >Berengarius</persName> divina favente clementi]a [<rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Notum sit omnibus
                        fideli]bus sancte Dei Ecclesie [nostrisque presentibus et futuris, qualiter
                        ob amorem Dei omnipoten]tis et ob reme[dium anime nostre nostrorumque
                        predecessorum perd]onavimus <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1402"
                            key="#Houses #Natural_landscape #Rivers #Mountains #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            >sancte <placeName ref="#places/505">Aritine</placeName>
                            ecclesie</orgName> in qua [beati Donati martir]is Christi corpus humatum
                        quiescit, cui etiam ecclesie <persName key="#Bishops #fidelisOf"
                            ref="#people/273">Petrus</persName> [venerabilis <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopus</rs> dilectu]sque <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs> noster
                        preesse dignoscitur, quandam <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sancti Marini</orgName> cum suis pertinentiis, et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >P[iu]nta</placeName> cum o[mnibus s]uis appenditiis, nec non <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Gratigiata</placeName> cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, sicut olim de <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1402">A[rit]ino</geogName> sub
                        integritate pertinuerunt una cum <rs key="#Houses">casis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">v[ineis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>,] pascuis,
                            <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, salectis, sacio[nibus], <rs
                            key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldionibus et aldianis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Natural_landscape">vallibus, planitiebus</rs> seu cum omnibus ad
                        eadem tria loca pertinentibus. Haec omnia de nostro iure et dominio in
                        prefate ecclesie ius et dominium omnino transfundimus atque donamus ad
                        habendum, tenendum, comutandum et fruendum, [qualib]et ecclesiastica censura
                        amota totius publice partis contraditione aut invasione vel molestia
                        cuiusquam. Si quis igitur hoc nostrum imperiale preceptum infringere vel
                        violare temtaverit, sciat se conpositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi
                            libras centum</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem camere
                            nostre</rs> et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem
                            Petro eiusdem ecclesie episcopo suisque successoribus</rs>. Quod ut
                        verius credatur et diligenitus observetur, manu propria roborantes de anulo
                        nostro subter insigniri iussimus. Signum domni (M) Beren[garii piissimi
                        imperatoris.] [<persName key="#Chancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/1501"
                            >Iohannes</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et] <rs key="#Chancellor"
                            >ca[ncellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"
                            ref="#people/216">Ardingi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi.] Data IIII non. Ian.,
                        anno dominice incarnatio[ni]s DCCCCXVI, domni vero Berengarii piissimi regis
                        XXVIII, imperii autem sui primo, indictione IIII. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/1082">Mucello</placeName>. In Christi nomine feliciter,
                        amen.</ab>
